<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="205" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,287,1611]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,685,711]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 15.8–18.1; head length: 1.5–1.7; head width: 3.0–3.4; pronotal length: 2.8–3.5; pronotal width: 9.8–10.7; scutellum length: 7.4–8.3; scutellum width: 5.5–6.0; abdominal width: 8.6–9.9; length of antennal segments. I: 0.9–1.0; II: 1.7–2.5; III: 1.4–2.2; IV: 4.1–4.5; V: 4.3–4.9.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="205" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,287,1611]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,792,818]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all or part of its extension; when stripe incomplete, remaining part smoky black and narrow. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[810,907,864,891]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777098/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 19I</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777098/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 19I</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[672,767,900,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777098/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 19J</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[965,1105,900,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dorsal rim excavated with a small triangular median projection (
<figureCitation box="[702,806,936,963]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup small and curved ventrally, ventral margin with digitiform expansion close to distal apex; adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[159,296,1008,1035]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere golf club like, elongated, strongly bent laterally; anterior lobe rounded and short; posterior lobe tapering, curved dorsally, and concave (
<figureCitation box="[663,800,1044,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11B–C</figureCitation>
); stalk with high carina on inner face ending at apex of posterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[324,460,1080,1107]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral dense tufts of setae separated by narrow glabrous carina; posterior face pentagonal (
<figureCitation box="[451,585,1116,1143]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11B–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim median excavation widely open and shallow; expansions little developed, rounded, strongly setose, just surpassing or level with posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1423,1152,1179]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[353,453,1188,1215]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 subtrapezoidal with posterior margin almost straight; inner angle reaching half of valvifers 9; inner margins divergent in distal half and dark. Valvulae 9 exposed. Valvifers 9 strongly setose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="205" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,287,1611]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1260,1286]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[620,771,1260,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trabeculus">
<emphasis box="[620,771,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. trabeculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[824,931,1260,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[824,931,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the paramere golf club like; posterior face of proctiger pentagonal; dorsal rim medially with a small convex expansion, and expansions of ventral rim with setae long and dense on apex (
<figureCitation box="[496,644,1332,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@19.[217,1371,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hypoxys pentagonalis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Figs. 11A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[656,742,1333,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777088" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777088/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">14A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[754,957,1332,1359]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" pagination="401 - 441" refId="ref18209" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. rest. (Heteroptera Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 401 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[833,890,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[968,1092,1332,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777076" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777076/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Fig. 8A–C</figureCitation>
). However, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1257,1437,1332,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1257,1437,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. pentagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the posterior process of the paramere is curved dorsolaterally (straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[962,1068,1368,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[962,1068,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1121,1273,1368,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trabeculus">
<emphasis box="[1121,1273,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. trabeculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The superior process of genital cup is curved with a distal digitiform process on ventral margin (straight in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1233,1387,1404,1430]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trabeculus">
<emphasis box="[1233,1387,1404,1430]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. trabeculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and curved but without ventral process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[584,693,1440,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[584,693,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The valvifers 8 of these species are very similar, especially the mesial distal excavation V-shaped, but the outer angles of distal margin are more angulated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1203,1382,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1203,1382,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">H. pentagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in the other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1157,1548,1575]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,287,1611]" box="[199,1157,1548,1575]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1549,1575]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the pentagonal form of the posterior face of the proctiger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
